  "slug": "angular-flex-layout-flexbox-and-grid-layout-for-angular-component",
  "locale": "ja",
  "properties": {
    "title": "Angular Flex-Layout: Flexbox and Grid Layout for Angular Component",
    "date": "2018-09-28T00:00:00.000Z",
    "category": "Tech",
    "tags": ["Angular"]
  },
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "CSS Flexbox",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and ",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "CSS Grid",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " are very powerful layout functions. These are already supported by all modern browsers except for IE 11. Unlike properties for styling (for example",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "color",
          "annotations": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and ",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "border",
          "annotations": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "), these are properties for ",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "building a layout structure",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". In other words, it is not used to beautify the surface of HTML elements but is used to create a foundation of application UI in cooperation with the hierarchical structure of HTML elements.",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "In Angular, it is common for a view of a component to be divided into ",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "template HTML",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and ",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "stylesheet CSS",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". Since the layout using Flexbox or Grid is closely related to the structure of HTML, it is not convenient that the layout settings are written in an external CSS file. So, it is a clever choice to define Flexbox and Grid settings in template HTML.",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Does it mean we should use inline style attributes? No!",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "This article explains how to use the ",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Angular Flex-Layout",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " module to build flexbox layout in Angular templates and its hidden features.",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Angular Flex-Layout",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Angular Flex-Layout is an npm package made by Angular team officially.",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "https://www.npmjs.com/package/%40angular%2Fflex-layout",
          "href": "https://www.npmjs.com/package/%40angular%2Fflex-layout",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " ",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Angular Flex Layout provides a sophisticated layout API using Flexbox CSS + mediaQuery. This module provides Angular developers with component layout features using a custom Layout API, mediaQuery observables, and injected DOM flexbox-2016 CSS stylings.",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Angular Flex-Layout provides some NgModules which exports directives. You can make a declarative layout structure by using Flexbox or CSS Grid.",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Installation",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Install the package with npm/yarn after creating a project with Angular CLI. Flex-Layout depends on Component DevKit (CDK), so you need additional installation if you haven‚Äôt installed it.",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "",
      "filename": "",
      "text": "$ yarn add @angular/flex-layout @angular/cdk"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "And add ",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "FlexLayoutModule",
          "annotations": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " into your ",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "AppModule",
          "annotations": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ".",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "",
      "filename": "",
      "text": "import { NgModule } from \"@angular/core\";\nimport { BrowserModule } from \"@angular/platform-browser\";\nimport { FlexLayoutModule } from \"@angular/flex-layout\";\n\nimport { AppComponent } from \"./app.component\";\nimport { CardComponent } from \"./card.component\";\n\n@NgModule({\n  imports: [BrowserModule, FlexLayoutModule],\n  declarations: [AppComponent, CardComponent],\n  bootstrap: [AppComponent]\n})\nexport class AppModule {}"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Installation is done! üéâ BTW, there is ",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "CardComponent",
          "annotations": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " in declarations of AppModule. It‚Äôs a component to display a simple card for the demonstration of Flexbox layout.",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "external": false,
      "url": "/src/content/images/angular-flex-layout-flexbox-and-grid-layout-for-angular-component/3c6255ea-b6c7-4055-8126-638d2819f0c3/e4a97ab4-0789-4625-8736-4400de17cb5f.png",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "",
      "filename": "",
      "text": "@Component({\n  selector: \"app-card\",\n  template: `\n    <div>Card: {{ name }}</div>\n  `,\n  styles: [\n    `\n      :host {\n        display: block;\n        padding: 32px;\n        border: 1px solid black;\n        border-radius: 8px;\n      }\n    `\n  ]\n})\nexport class CardComponent {}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Making a Flexbox¬†layout",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "We‚Äôre ready to make a component with Flexbox layouts! Let‚Äôs learn about Flexbox APIs of Angular Flex-Layout via some example cases.",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Example 1. Column-based card list",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": true
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The best simple example is a column-based list. It can be implemented with plain CSS like below;",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "external": false,
      "url": "/src/content/images/angular-flex-layout-flexbox-and-grid-layout-for-angular-component/3c6255ea-b6c7-4055-8126-638d2819f0c3/3f8ba4fc-99ba-4ef5-b422-d47b45762c57.png",
      "caption": "Column-based card¬†list"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "filename": "",
      "text": "<style>\n  .cardList {\n    display: flex;\n    flex-direction: column;\n  }\n  /* Row Gap */\n  .cardList > *:not(:last-child) {\n    margin-bottom: 32px;\n  }\n</style>\n\n<div class=\"cardList\">\n  <app-card></app-card>\n  <app-card></app-card>\n  <app-card></app-card>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Flexbox container is defined with ",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "display: flex",
          "annotations": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and its direction is defined with ",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "flex-direction",
          "annotations": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "property. To define the gap between each row,¬†",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ":not(:last-child)",
          "annotations": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " selector is needed because CSS‚Äôs Flexbox doesn‚Äôt support gap size configuration. It‚Äôs a bit verbose styling.",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "With Angular Flex-Layout, the same layout will be implemented as following template;",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "filename": "",
      "text": "<div fxLayout=\"column\" fxLayoutGap=\"32px\">\n  <app-card></app-card>\n  <app-card></app-card>\n  <app-card></app-card>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "As you can see, there is a Flexbox container with ",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "fxLayout=\"column\"",
          "annotations": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and configuration of it. Isn‚Äôt it intuitive? In the above example, 2 directives are used to create a Flexbox container.",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulleted_list",
      "items": [
        {
          "type": "bulleted_list_item",
          "text": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "fxLayout=‚Äùcolumn‚Äù",
              "annotations": {
                "code": true
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " ‚ÄîCorresponding to ",
              "annotations": {}
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "display: flex",
              "annotations": {
                "code": true
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and ",
              "annotations": {}
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "flex-direction",
              "annotations": {
                "code": true
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "¬†.",
              "annotations": {}
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "\nCreate a new Flexbox container and setting its direction",
              "annotations": {}
            }
          ],
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "type": "bulleted_list_item",
          "text": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "fxLayoutGap=‚Äù32px‚Äù",
              "annotations": {
                "code": true
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " ‚ÄîCorresponding to ",
              "annotations": {}
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "margin-bottom: 32px",
              "annotations": {
                "code": true
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "\nfor each child except the last.",
              "annotations": {}
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "\nConfigure the gap size between each item",
              "annotations": {}
            }
          ],
          "children": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Example 2. Row-based card list",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": true
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Another example is a row-based card list with 3 columns. It‚Äôs a common UI pattern used with small cards.",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "external": false,
      "url": "/src/content/images/angular-flex-layout-flexbox-and-grid-layout-for-angular-component/3c6255ea-b6c7-4055-8126-638d2819f0c3/d1027398-b212-4f65-88a1-42bc2d6d67ea.png",
      "caption": "Row-based card¬†list"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "To implement that with plain CSS, the template will become like below;",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "filename": "",
      "text": "<style>\n  .cardList {\n    display: flex;\n    flex-direction: row;\n    flex-wrap: wrap;\n    justify-content: flex-start;\n  }\n  /* Column Gap */\n  .cardList > * {\n    box-sizing: border-box;\n  }\n  .cardList > *:not(:last-child) {\n    margin-right: 32px;\n  }\n  /* Item sizing */\n  .cardListItem {\n    flex: 0 1 calc(33.3% - 32px);\n  }\n</style>\n\n<div class=\"cardList\">\n  <ng-container *ngFor=\"let _ of [1,2,3,4,5,6]\">\n    <app-card class=\"cardListItem\"></app-card>\n  </ng-container>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "And rewritten template with Angular Flex-Layout is the below;",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "filename": "",
      "text": "<div fxLayout=\"row wrap\" fxLayoutGap=\"32px\" fxLayoutAlign=\"flex-start\">\n  <ng-container *ngFor=\"let _ of [1,2,3,4,5,6]\">\n    <app-card fxFlex=\"0 1 calc(33.3% - 32px)\"></app-card>\n  </ng-container>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "It‚Äôs very cool! üòé In this case, there is a container with ",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "fxLayout=\"row wrap\"",
          "annotations": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "¬†. The",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "fxLayout",
          "annotations": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " directive can take a wrapping configuration as the second parameter. And I added the",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "fxFlex",
          "annotations": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " directive for each element to adjust its width to align as 3 columns.",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulleted_list",
      "items": [
        {
          "type": "bulleted_list_item",
          "text": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "fxLayoutAlign=‚Äùflex-start‚Äù",
              "annotations": {
                "code": true
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäCorresponding to ",
              "annotations": {}
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "justify-content: flex-start",
              "annotations": {
                "code": true
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ".",
              "annotations": {}
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "\nConfigure alignment of the Flexbox container",
              "annotations": {}
            }
          ],
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "type": "bulleted_list_item",
          "text": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "fxFlex=\"1 0 auto\"",
              "annotations": {
                "code": true
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäCorresponding to ",
              "annotations": {}
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "flex: 1 0 auto",
              "annotations": {
                "code": true
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ".",
              "annotations": {}
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "\nConfigure its CSS ",
              "annotations": {}
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "flex",
              "annotations": {
                "code": true
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " properties",
              "annotations": {}
            }
          ],
          "children": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Responsive APIs",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The previous row-based example has a problem with the mobile viewport. Let‚Äôs make its card size responsive!",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "external": false,
      "url": "/src/content/images/angular-flex-layout-flexbox-and-grid-layout-for-angular-component/3c6255ea-b6c7-4055-8126-638d2819f0c3/5cf6ea19-aa26-4f30-a390-1b13318410a4.gif",
      "caption": "Responsive Columns"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "To implement this, you have to use CSS media queries and define breakpoints in order to determine which size is small or medium. A natural implementation may become like below;",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "filename": "",
      "text": "<style>\n  .cardList {\n    display: flex;\n    flex-direction: row;\n    flex-wrap: wrap;\n    justify-content: flex-start;\n  }\n  /* Column Gap */\n  .cardList > * {\n    box-sizing: border-box;\n  }\n  .cardList > *:not(:last-child) {\n    margin-right: 32px;\n  }\n  /* Item sizing */\n  .cardListItem {\n    flex: 0 1 calc(33.3% - 32px);\n  }\n  /* medium size viewport */\n  @media screen and (max-width: 959px) {\n    /* Column Gap */\n    .cardList > *:not(:last-child) {\n      margin-right: 32px;\n    }\n    /* Item sizing */\n    .cardListItem {\n      flex: 0 1 calc(50% - 32px);\n    }\n  }\n  /* small size viewport */\n  @media screen and (max-width: 599px) {\n    .cardList {\n      display: flex;\n      flex-direction: column;\n      justify-content: flex-start;\n    }\n    .cardList > *:not(:last-child) {\n      margin-right: unset;\n      margin-bottom: 32px;\n    }\n  }\n</style>"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "I‚Äôm not sure how long time I can maintain this CSS‚Ä¶ üòá",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Don‚Äôt worry!",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " Angular Flex-Layout also provides APIs to support responsive UI! You don‚Äôt have to install any additional modules. Angular Flex-Layout supports Responsive APIs ",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "as an enhancement",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " of Static APIs.",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Angular Flex-Layout directives can take a breakpoint alias as the syntax; ",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "<directive>.<breakpoint alias>",
          "annotations": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". For example, ",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "fxLayout.lt-sm=\"column\"",
          "annotations": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " will be applied only when the viewport is ",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "less than small",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". This enhancement gives us a very maintainable code which is easy to read and write.",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Here is the rewritten code. Super simple and declarative!",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "filename": "",
      "text": "<div\n  fxLayout=\"row wrap\"\n  fxLayout.lt-sm=\"column\"\n  fxLayoutGap=\"32px\"\n  fxLayoutAlign=\"flex-start\"\n>\n  <ng-container *ngFor=\"let _ of [1,2,3,4,5,6]\">\n    <app-card\n      fxFlex=\"0 1 calc(33.3% - 32px)\"\n      fxFlex.lt-md=\"0 1 calc(50% - 32px)\"\n      fxFlex.lt-sm=\"100%\"\n    ></app-card>\n  </ng-container>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Each child element has new ",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
